The paper deals with combinatorial auctions, which are a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on best-response dynamics suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), while the analysis of welfare guarantees is related to computational complexity and optimization (cs.EC). Finally, the use of mathematical techniques and proofs indicates a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
